<dl id="n30172f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30172f">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30172f"> 172(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sitting room / lying room / standing room / kneeling room / lolling room</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">When a person is sleepless from trying to go to sleep in a stuffy room in which perhaps he has been working all day <mark>(a bed-sitting room; studio-bedroom; bed in the study)</mark>, then a brisk walk in the open air is often found all that is necessary. <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 48-9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
